
[1]guava

   GU`AVA, n. An American tree,and its fruit, of the genus Psidium. It is
   of two species,or rather varieties, the pyriferum or white guava, and
   pomiferum or red guava. The fruit or berry is large and oval-shaped,
   like a pomegranate, which it resembles in its astringent quality. The
   pulp is of an agreeable flavor,and of this fruit is made a delicious
   jelly.
